Section 1:
1 L.D. 214
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 MARINE RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 137, L.D. 214, “An Act to Create a For-
10 hire Charter Boat Operator License and to Require Individuals Recreationally Fishing for
11 Halibut in Coastal Waters to Register with the Saltwater Recreational Fishing Registry”
12 Amend the bill in section 5 in §6313 in subsection 4 by striking out all of paragraph A
13 (page 2, lines 9 and 10 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
14 'A. Possesses a valid United States merchant marine document issued by the United
15 States Coast Guard for an operator of uninspected passenger vessel or master or mate
16 captain's license; or'
17 Amend the bill by inserting after section 5 the following:
18 'Sec. 6. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.'
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment corrects language referencing the United States Coast Guard and adds
2233 an effective date of January 1, 2026.
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0356(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
